https://leetcode.com/problems/subarray-sum-equals-k/description/

QUESTION:
Input: nums = [1,2,3], k = 3
Output: 2

SOLUTION:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
TIME COMPLEXITY:O(n)
SPACE COMPLEXITY:O(n)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Intuition: If (rsum - k) was seen before, then a subarray with sum k exists ending here.
Step 1: Start with:
        Running sum = 0
        Count = 0
Step 2: Map contains {0:1} (to handle subarrays starting from index 0)
        Move through the array one element at a time:
        Add current number to running sum
Step3:  Compute: running sum − k
        This tells you what previous sum you need
Step 4: Check the map:
        If that value exists → it means a subarray ending here has sum = k
        Add its frequency to count
Step 5: Update the map:
        Store current running sum
        Increase its frequency

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CODE:
class Solution {
    public int subarraySum(int[] nums, int k) {
        if(nums==null || nums.length==0)return 0;
        int count=0,rSum=0;
        HashMap<Integer,Integer>map=new HashMap<>();
        map.put(0,1);
        for(int i=0;i<nums.length;i++)
        {
            rSum+=nums[i];
            int compliment=rSum-k;
            if(map.containsKey(compliment))
            {
                count+=map.get(compliment);
            }
            if(!map.containsKey(rSum))
            {
                map.put(rSum,1);
            }
            else
            {
                map.put(rSum,map.get(rSum)+1);
            }
        }
        return count;
    }
}
